# Hotel Mnagement System Database 
---The Hotel Management System Database is a relational database project designed
to manage the core operations of a hotel, including customer management,
room allocation, booking records, and payment tracking.
---This project demonstrates how structured databases help hotels organize operational data
efficiently, maintain room availability, and manage reservations with accuracy.
---The database is implemented using SQL and follows database normalization and relational design
principles to ensure data consistency, integrity, and efficient querying.
🗃️Database Normalization
---1NF – Eliminates repeating groups
---2NF – Removes partial dependency
---3NF – Eliminates transitive dependency
⚙️ Technologies Used
---MySQL
---SQL Queries
---Relational Database Design
---Primary Keys & Foreign Keys
---Joins and Constraints
📊 Use Cases
---Hotel reservation management
---Customer data management
---Booking and room allocation
---Financial transaction tracking
📌 Learning Outcomes
---Database schema design
---SQL query writing
---Data normalization
---Table relationships and constraints
---Data retrieval using joins
